  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> basmati rice </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606824775904-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606824775904-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606824775904-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606824775904-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606824775904-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, bash the <strong>cardamom pods</strong> and remove the <strong>seeds </strong>from the shells</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>fennel seeds</strong> (not a fan of aniseed? Only add a little!), <strong>cardamom seeds</strong> and most of the <strong>cumin seeds </strong>(save some for later!)</p><p>Toast for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1606824782903-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1606824782903-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1606824782903-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1606824782903-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1606824782903-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the spices are toasting, add the <strong>lamb mince</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and<strong> remaining cumin seeds</strong> to a bowl</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Divide the <strong>lamb mince</strong> into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> and shape into meatballs </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1606824817689-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1606824817689-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1606824817689-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1606824817689-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1606824817689-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>toasted spices</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar </strong>and return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>lamb meatballs </strong>and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
