    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Once the meatballs are cooked through, remove the pan from the heat and stir through the <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> with <strong>most</strong> of the <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Set aside for 2 min until the yoghurt has warmed through – this is your <strong>Kashmiri-style lamb meatball curry</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong> over the <strong>basmati rice</strong> (don't mix it!) and set aside for 2 min</p>",
